# Frontend Project-Specific Conventions

## Panel Components

Each generation type (Code, Text, Image, Audio, Unity Project) should have its own panel component:

- Place components in `frontend/src/components/`
- Follow naming convention: `{Type}Panel.vue` (e.g., `CodePanel.vue`, `TextPanel.vue`)
- Each panel should handle its own state and API calls
- Use consistent structure: prompt input, provider/model options, generate button, result display

## Status Banner

Use `StatusBanner` component for consistent status/error display:

- Import from `./StatusBanner.vue`
- Pass `status` (string | null) and `tone` ("ok" | "error") props
- Display status messages consistently across all panels

## API Client

All backend communication goes through `api/client.ts` functions:

- Import functions from `../api/client` or `@/api/client`
- Use typed request/response interfaces matching backend schemas
- Handle errors consistently with try/catch blocks
- Update status refs based on response success/failure

Available API functions:
- `generateCode(request)`
- `generateText(request)`
- `generateImage(request)`
- `generateAudio(request)`
- `generateUnityProject(request)`
- `saveApiKeys(keys)`
- `setPref(key, value)`
- `getPref(key)`
- `getLatestOutput()`
- `healthCheck()`

## Backend URL Configuration

- Store backend URL in localStorage with key `backendUrl`
- Use fallback to `http://127.0.0.1:8000` if not set
- Access via `getBackendUrl()` function in `api/client.ts`

## Testing

- Use Vitest for unit tests
- Use Playwright for E2E tests (in `frontend/tests/e2e/`)
- Use descriptive test names that explain what is being tested
- Follow Arrange-Act-Assert pattern
- Test components in isolation when possible

## Component File Structure

Follow this structure for panel components:

```typescript
<script setup lang="ts">
// 1. Imports
// 2. Type definitions (if needed)
// 3. Reactive state (refs)
// 4. Validation functions
// 5. API call functions
// 6. Lifecycle hooks
</script>

<template>
  <!-- Component template -->
</template>

<style scoped>
/* Component-specific styles */
</style>
```
